The state machine should transition from BYTE1 to BYTE2 if the third bit of the input is 1, from BYTE2 to BYTE3, and from BYTE3 to DONE. If the third bit of the input is 0, the state machine should transition from BYTE1 to BYTE1 and from DONE to BYTE1. The done signal should be set to 1 when the state machine is in the DONE state. 

The out_bytes output should be set to the contents of the register when the done signal is set to 1.

